e> Untitled work</span><hr size=1> I am new to posting on these boards, but I have admired the great works of writing I have noticed in this area, especially the works by Riverdane.  I fancy myself someone who has a decent talent in the use of words to convey thoughts and ideas, as well as conjuring up stories for people to read.  I sometimes post my works on my guild boards.  Lately I have been writing a longer story on my guild boards, which I have become fairly drawn into.<br>
<br>
A while back, I was in the Plane of Hate, on a raid with RoK.  I did a /who in the zone, and I noticed a familliar name in the zone, one who's writing intrigued me; Riverdane.  I sent him a tell saying how much I admired his work, and told him that I am also a decent writer myself.  I mentioned that I may actually get up the guts to posting on these boardsone day soon.  Well, I've finally gotten up the guts to post.<br>
<br>
As of yet, this story is untitled.  I have been unable to think of a decent name for it.  Naming my stories has always been a problem for me.  Anyways.....  The story is still a work in progress.  I will post new additions periodically.  I hope you will enjoy it.  Now enough of my gnomish rambling, ON WITH THE SHOW! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
_____________________________________________<br>
<br>
Tick, tock. Tick, tock. Tick tock.<br>
<br>
I slowly opened my eyes and my ears received the comforting sounds of the clock on the wall. Whenever I feel lost or scared or lonely, the sound of the ticking in my heart can always soothe my mind. I thought about this as my mind relaxed and took in my surroundings. My house was in disorder. I had books laying across the floor, covered with a topping of papers. A chair leaned against the wall, as if pushed out of the way in a hurry. And clothes were scattered about everywhere. <br>
<br>
&quot;I really must clean this place up a little.&quot; I thought to myself as I picked up my worn travelling robe resting next to the bed. The robe was mostly red with stripes of yellow and orange pasted across the front. Magic of old held the threads together, making them near impossible to break, but years of wear had finally started to fray the hem of it. &quot;It won't be long and some threads will begin to unravel&quot; I again thought.<br>
<br>
A knock at the door brought me to attention. &quot;Be right there!&quot; I yelled to the visitor. I hurredly put on my travelling robe and stumbled over to the door. I must remember to not drink that much gnomish spirits again i realized.<br>
<br>
An impatient knock rang out. &quot;Hold on or I will feed you to Jabober!&quot; I shouted.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bah, just hurry up and answer the door Shorty.&quot; answered a familliar voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not short! I'm vertically challenged you big oaf!&quot; I said as I reached the door. I grasped the handle and puuled the door open to cast a glimpse on the barbarian standing in the doorway with his hands over his ears.<br>
<br>
&quot;How can you stand all this infernal racket? I can't hear myself think, nevertheless hear others talk.&quot; the barbarian said as his hands waved around him. &quot;I hate Ak'anon. You gnomes are odd.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well you stink. I think it's time for your yearly bath Joramen.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Watch it or I'll eat you! You would fit nice in my belly.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Bah!&quot;<br>
<br>
I walked back in towards my house and Joramen followed, ducking low to get through the door. &quot;I hate Ak'anon! I can't even walk in a gnome house without having to duck.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Quit your complaining. Halas isn't such a resort town in my opinion...&quot;<br>
<br>
Joramen glared at me, &quot;What was that??&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You heard me. Now what is it you want?&quot;<br>
<br>
Joramen gave a little grunt and said, &quot;We need your help. A bunch of us are heading to Western Wastes to fight some dragons and we need more to come along with us. You game?&quot;<br>
<br>
A flash of excitement passed through my eyes and a smile crept up my cheeks. &quot;Dragons... Sounds like tons of fun!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Meet us tomorrow in the Nexus shortly after sunrise. This shall give us plenty of time for travel and hunting.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ok, I will be there friend.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Good. See you later Boppy.&quot; Joramen headed for the door, raising his hands to his ears.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hate that name! My name is Jimbop of Akanon, Do not address me as Boppy.....&quot;  Joramen was out the door without hearing a word I said, so I gave up talking.  Ahh, dragon hunting. Tomorrow will be a good day.<br>
