<br>
People of all races crowded through the Nexus on this day, hustling between their destinations. A high elf maiden, in a long flowing green dress, was casting KEI to all those who required it's use, in exchange for 100 platinum piece. A grinning, and especially hairy, halfling hawked his wares next to a couple Nexus guardians donned in gleaming white armor. A wart-faced troll let out a roar of laughter while conversing with a straggly-looking human with a lute in hand and a dark skinned wizard. My gnomish eyes scanned the bustling and busy crowd, searching for a particular group of people I was supposed to meet up with.<br>
<br>
I headed towards the Bazaar, a place where many people go to sell rare and unusual items, to seek what I desired, only to find a sleeping dwarf, whose snoring is loud enough to make one go deaf. A nearby dark elf glared evily at the dwarf, but upon seeing the ancient breastplate across his cheast, the battle-worn sword resting next to his gnarled hand, and the hint of white in the dwarf's beard, decided against whatever his evilish mind had planned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where is everyone?&quot; I thought. Late again, I assume. Impatience began to set into my brain after a couple of seconds, for gnomes generally don't like to wait around. I sat down on a stair near the Kunark portal and waited.<br>
<br>
A voice rang out through the Nexus, &quot;Everyone traveling to Kunark, please step onto the portal now.&quot;<br>
<br>
The sleeping dwarf woke up suddenly, and as if he had never ben truely asleep, stood up, and walked over to the Kunark pad. I smiled, knowing that this dwarf is a veteran of many, many battles with vicious foes and is trained to be awake when actually asleep. My thoughts drift back to the dark elf and what would have happened had the dark elf taken action. My thoughts were soon interrupted...<br>
<br>
&quot;Boppy!&quot; a female voice rang out from behind me.<br>
<br>
&quot;My name's NOT Boppy, Siara! I'm Jimbop of Akanon, elementalist of......&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, of course you are, Boppy. Anyways, glad to see you here! We were wondering where you were.&quot;<br>
<br>
I stand up and turn around to face Siara. A druid princess of 60 seasons, the beautiful wood elf walked up to me. A smile draped across her narrow face, and her slender nose twiched just slightly when a giggle emitted from her full-bodied lips. Narrow eye sockets beamed blue when her long brown hair wasn't blocking them. With a quick whisp of her hand, the hair instead tried to hide her shoulders.<br>
<br>
&quot;Are you ready to come with us Boppy?&quot;<br>
<br>
I sigh, knowing I will never be able to get them to stop calling me 'Boppy.' &quot;Yes, I am ready.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Follow me over to everyone else, and we will port out.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ok.&quot;<br>
<br>
I follow her up the stairs and back into the center of the Nexus. We cross the room and head into another hallway with a new assortment of beings, except these are beings I know.<br>
<br>
With a quick bow, I said hello to Joramen, Galmor, Caenyien, Frequency, Tarimus, Tensheba, and Fisbik. Joramen and Galmor, the 2 barbarian brutes, stood next to one another in newly polished breastplates. Caenyien, a high elf, sat on the ground, reading his book on healing. Frequency, a half-elf, sat near Caenyien, composing a new song in his songbook. Tarimus, awood elf ranger, and Tensheba, a vah shir shaman faced each other, involved in an engrossing conversation. Lastly, Fisbik, a gnome, was looking at his spellbook, trying to find his teleportation spells. Such a diverse group, yet all are like family to one another through the guild name we carry in our hearts.<br>
<br>
I am greeted by every one of them in return. &quot;Well, let's get going. We don't got all day.&quot; said Joramen.<br>
<br>
Everyone stood up and gathered into a circle. Siara and Fisbik began to chant whispered words only they could understand. Each one whispered a list of names in between spidery words, names of our group. Half of our groups names were whispered by Siara and half by Fisbik, for a mortal is only able to transport 5 others at one time. The whispers grew faster and faster. Bright blue balls of energy appeared in the air surrounding the group and swirled around. The hair on the back of my neck began to rise as magical energy flowed into my skin. Bumps appeared my skin and the outside world began to fade away from view...<br>
